title.73: Sgt. Fury and His Howling Commandos Annual (1965) #1

description.0: Will Nick Fury suffer the fool as a mind slave of Mentallo? Not if Dum Dum Dugan can help it! S.H.I.E.L.D. plans a counterattack against two psychic foes. Doc Strange leaves his physical body behind...and ends up losing it!
description.1: While being arrested for the use of the Enervation Intensifier, Tony Stark is suddenly transported through time and space. But where will he end up?
description.2: Seidring has been unleashed upon Asgard, casting doom over divine and mortal being alike. Will the son of Odin rise to defeat this latest menace? The Odin Power may be strong with Seidring, but the Mighty Thunderer has clout all his own!
description.4: Behold…Galactus continues!  The Fantastic Four must work together to save the Earth from the evil hands of Galactus! Meanwhile, the Silver Surfer's motives are weakened by the wonders of Alicia Masters and he decides to defeat his master!
description.9: Enter Kraven the Hunter! Kraven has isolated himself in the wilderness to brew and plot revenge against Spider-Man. When Kraven returns to New York to hunt down his prey, Spider-Man is caught unawares.
description.10: Daredevil heads across the pond! After the Plunderer involves Ka-Zar and Matt in his next plot, the two heroes find themselves in London embroiled in a heist operation. Will Plunderer be able to filch his family out of an inheritance? And will Daredevil be able to subdue a thief gone rogue? It all culminates in one shocking ending that spells bad news for Ka-Zar!
description.12: Mentallo and Fixer combine their power for one dangerous attack. S.H.I.E.L.D. can't sense them coming, and Fury is taken unawares. This is one time the good guys can't win! Strange drops into his astral form, getting the drop on Demonicus.
description.13: When using the Enervation Intensifier device in order to heal Happy Hogan of his wounds, Iron Man accidentally transforms his friend and body guard into a horrible creature dubbed "The Freak".
description.14: Thor vs. Hercules! The heavens rumble as two gods do battle...for the love of one mortal woman! Meanwhile, Odin inflicts his punishment on Thor.
description.16: The First Appearance of Silver Surfer and Galactus!  Introducing the World-Eater and his enigmatic herald, the Silver Surfer, as the Fantastic Four stand in defense of Earth in one of the most beloved sagas ever told!
description.19: Steve Ditko buries Spidey, mirroring a scene from the book's interior--one that would go on to help define Spider-Man for all time.
description.20: Stranded and unconscious in the Savage Land, Daredevil finds himself at the mercy of Maa-Gor, brutal leader to the Man-Apes. Will Daredevil be able to stave off this threat despite his lack of powers? Plus, the mysterious origin of Ka-Zar is revealed by Plunderer, and Karen Page worries over Matt's disappearance.
description.21: While Thor is in Asgard facing the punishment of revealing himself to Jane, Hercules is in New York City charming all who surround him. Is the punishment Thor faces for telling Jane the truth worth it, especially when he finds her on a date with Hercules?!
description.23: S.H.I.E.L.D.'s battle with Hydra comes to a head, leading to the death of a key player. Plus, what is Operation Brain Blast? S.H.I.E.L.D. delves into the realm of the supernatural with a new ESP division. Will Fury become the first unwilling subject? Doctor Strange reaches an agreement with Dormammu. Clea is banished to a much darker dimension.
description.24: When Iron Man is left for dead by the Black Knight, he calls upon Pepper Potts to come to his rescue.
description.26: The Fantastic Four meet up with Black Bolt in this issue and have discovered a way to track down the Inhumans!
description.32: The true identity of the Master Planner revealed! But why is the villain collecting radioactive materials? And what's with those strange experiments? Plus, Peter continues to deal with the stresses of Aunt May's illness and the pressures of being a full-time student.
description.33: The Man without Fear takes on the Plunderer, infamous pirate of the high seas! But what has brought the Plunderer aboard a cruise ship? And where is he planning on taking Matt Murdock? As Daredevil, Matt saves wild man Ka-Zar from a carnivorous plant of the Savage Land!
description.34: Donald Blake FINALLY reveals his true identity as Thor to Jane Foster!
description.36: The Imperial Hydra revealed! Who is Hydra's Head of Terror, and what will he do when the Betatron bomb is activated? Agent G makes her full defection to S.H.I.E.L.D., while Tony Stark saves the day! All the lords and ladies of the mystical realm watch Doctor Strange duel with Dormammu.
description.37: Iron Man learns that Hogan has been kidnapped from the hospital, and he follows the clues to a secret castle.
description.39: While the Fantastic Four are fighting the Inhumans, someone called "The Seeker" arrives. They learn that The Seeker is trying to bring back those who have escaped from the Great Refuge! The Fantastic Four soon recognize another captive of The Seeker... Triton!
description.42: The First Appearance of Gwen Stacy and Harry Osborn! Spider-Man starts college! But before he does, the web-slinger must track down some crooks who have recently acquired nuclear cargo. With Aunt May ill at home, and Peter's personal life in disarray, will Spider-Man be able to tackle freshman year and a new villain by the name of Master Planner?
description.43: Who is the mysterios Organizer?  And can Daredevil stop primal threats the likes of Frog-Man, Bird Man and more animal themed evil?
description.44: Loki has earned Odin's scepter after the Absorbing Man bests the All-Father!
description.46: Nick Fury gets an unlikely assist from Agent G, the Imperial Hydra's daughter. The Imperial Hydra must find out where Braino-saur is, the only machine that can disrupt the Betatron bomb! In his strange tale, Doctor Strange does battle with Baron Mordo.
description.47: Returning to America following his battle against the Titanium Man, Iron Man begins to worry over the fate of his bodyguard Happy Hogan, who was critically injured in that battle.
description.49: The First Appearance of the Inhumans!  Johnny meets a girl name Crystal and soon discovers she is Inhuman! Upon meeting her family, Johnny recognizes Medusa and immediately calls the Fantastic Four for backup. Their mysterious leader Black Bolt arrives and the two teams face off!
description.51: A fashion show in France - sounds like fun, right? It is, until the theft of a designer's work turns Millie into a prime suspect.
description.55: An enigmatic thief known as the Cat Burglar has robbed J. Jonah Jameson, and Spider-Man is after the reward for his capture!
description.56: Thor is blackmailed by reporter Harris Hobbs, who has snagged pictures of the Thunder God transitioning from Thor to Don Blake!
description.58: The First Appearance of Eternity!  Doctor Strange meets the living embodiment of Eternity in his mystic adventures. Plus, failing to disable Hydra's Betatron bomb, S.H.I.E.L.D. calls in the assistance of none other than Tony Stark! Stark knows weapons, but does he know Hydra?
description.59: Happy Hogan has been critically injured bringing a new component for Iron Man's armor to the battle field... where the Golden Avenger is battling the Titanium Man.
description.61: When Johnny discovers the escaped Medusa hiding in his car, she demands he drive her out of the city! However, they can't seem to escape the evil Gorgon, who has come for Medusa!
description.65: The return of the Scorpion! The deadly villain has sworn vengeance on Spider-Man and J. Jonah Jameson, and will stop at nothing to destroy them both!
description.66: Animal-themed criminals are causing a wave of crime and it will be up to Dardevil to put an end to the madness.
description.67: The wedding of Sue and Reed! Note: This 24-page digital comic features the original content from this issue, and does not include the reprints of Fantastic Four #6 & #11 that appeared in the 1965 print edition.
description.68: Battle rages on between Thor and the Absorbing Man, who is taking on the properties of many surrounding structures in the city! Jane Foster remains kidnapped by an unknown caper.
description.69: Sgt. Fury and the Howling Commandos travel the Burma Road to rescue Sister Theresa and her orphans.
description.70: Hydra assumes the position for a full-on nuclear launch. The target? All of Earth's nations! The clock is ticking as Fury must disable Hydra's Betatron bomb. Comrades Gabe Jones and Dum Dum Dugan assist! After probing the mind of the Ancient One, Doctor Strange gets closer to Eternity.
description.71: Accepting a challenge from the Titanium Man in combat to prove which nation's armored champion is superior, Iron Man soon finds that the Titanium Man is not playing a fair game, having rigged the battle field with landmines.
description.72: When the Frightful Four comes into contact with Reed and Sue, they try to brainwash them as well! Reed performs  surgery on Ben to get him out of his trance and the team must fight together to capture the Frightful Four! The only problem is one of them manages to escape...
description.73: Sgt. Nick Fury takes on D-Day...
description.80: Thor arrives back on Midgard as Don Blake, to discover his medical practice empty and Jane Foster nowhere to be found!
description.81: The Howling Commandos and McGiveney's Maulers are sent to Ploesti to destroy artillery in advance of the bombing raid on the German oil supply stored there.
description.82: Nick Fury, captured by Hydra! Will S.H.I.E.L.D.'s fiercest agent reveal his operation's HQ? Not on your life! Fury pulls the wool over Hydra's eyes. Doctor Strange must save the woman he loves from Dormammu and his Mindless Ones.
description.83: Tony struggles with Pepper's relationship with Happy as he is sent into battle in Alberia.
description.85: With the already brainwashed Thing, the Frightful Four capture and brainwash the Torch! They're on a mission to capture the entire Fantastic Four team!
description.86: The menace of the Molten Man! Learn the origin of Spider-Man's strangest new foe!
description.90: Is there a doctor who can restore Matt Murdock's sight?  Before he can even process that decision, Daredevil leaps into action to prevent an assassination.
description.91: Loki and Karnilla are able to awaken Odin from his Odinsleep, who immediately rushes to Thor's aid against the Destroyer!
description.92: Fury and the Commandos travel to Czechoslovakia to rescue the daughter of a weapons designer.
description.93: S.H.I.E.L.D.'s first appearance! Long considered S.H.I.E.L.D.'s definitive adversary, Hydra has brought their own brand of terror to the Marvel Universe since 1965. Check out Nick Fury vs. Hydra's many heads! Plus, an adventure with Doctor Strange leads him to the Dark Dimension.
description.94: Having returned from Ireland, Happy Hogan resumes work at Stark Industries, and Tony Stark gets a letter from his cousin Morgan asking for help.
description.95: The brutal betrayal of Ben Grimm! The Frightful Four kidnap the Thing and force him into helping them defeat the rest of his team!  Will they win?
description.96: Spider-Man has been captured by the Green Goblin and is at the mercy of the mob! Plus, the final confrontation with the Crime-Master!  Will he reveal the Green Goblin's identity?

3.text: He's got all of the X-Men's powers but none of their sanity: the Mimic! He's out to join the team or destroy it, and he doesn't really care which!

8.text: The Wasp is captured by Attuma, who threatens to flood the world with his Wave Machine! It's up to the Avengers to stop him, of course!

11.text: Check out Stan Lee's final issue on "Sgt. Fury"! For the first time, we see a Nazi display remorse…

15.text: Magneto sends the X-Men on a balloon ride of death! Only Iceman remains to challenge him!

16.text: "The Coming of Galactus" begins here! As the Fantastic Four struggle to understand what the Silver Surfer's appearance means, they must steel themselves for what's ahead--Galactus, the devourer of worlds!
The FF were a cosmic quartet from the get-go, but "The Coming of Galacus" solidified their place in the Marvel U. as official masters of all otherworldly problems.

17.text: The Hulk finds himself in a dystopian future, attacked by an army of King Arrkam's warriors!

18.text: Fooled into visiting Latveria by a spurious letter from their aunt, Quicksilver, the Scarlet Witch, and the rest of the Avengers are jailed, left at the whims of the country's iron-fisted (and faced) ruler - Doctor Doom!

19.text: A beaten, bruised and nearly broken Spider-Man overcomes all obstacles in his way, pushing past all known limits to survive and fight another day.
Steve Ditko buries Spidey, mirroring a scene from the book's interior--one that would go on to help define Spider-Man for all time.

22.text: The reason behind Fury's eyepatch, revealed in this issue!

25.text: The first Sentinel Saga is over, but metal can be dangerous even when it's not in the form of robots! Just ask...Magneto!

30.text: What will the Hulk do with the Watcher's Ultimate Machine?

31.text: The Avengers are up against insurmountable odds when Kang the Conqueror's endless army attacks. But when his own troops attempt an insurrection, Kang and the Avengers must join forces to save Princess Ravonna, Kang's unwilling bride-to-be!

35.text: A U.S. crew has been captured aboard a Nazi ship! If there is any bright side however, it's that "Dum-Dum" Dugan has a plan.

38.text: Have the Sentinels triumphed over the X-Men, or will they be struck down from within their own ranks? Before it's over, someone will die!

41.text: Captain America has left the Avengers! But when Kang the Conqueror abducts the remaining team and imprisons them in his future, who else can save them but the Star-Spangled Avenger?

45.text: Sergeant Nick Fury is surrounded, but if we've learned one thing, never EVER count him out.

48.text: Part Two of the first X-Men vs. Sentinels storyline! The world's strangest teens have penetrated the rogue robots' citadel, but it'll be a lot harder to escape!

54.text: Disgraced and disbanded, the troubles continue as the Avengers try to clear their good names. And for Captain America, that means a showdown with Power Man! But even if the team is found innocent, will it be enough to keep them intact?

57.text: Nick Fury's Fighting Fanatics on furlough?! Surely this cannot be!

60.text: For the first time, the Sentinels walk the Earth! To protect humanity from mutantkind, they've decided to conquer the world - and only the X-Men can stop them!

64.text: The Avengers are tricked into the endangering the innocent by the Enchantress' illusions - but will anyone realize the real menace to society before it's too late? Introducing the Avengers' newest foe - Power Man!

74.text: A vile new foe has hatched a plot to steal the Wand of Watoomb from Doctor Strange! Spider-Man fights the Circus of Crime!  All this and more in a super-sized spectacular! (note: this issue does not contain the reprinted stories originally printed)

78.text: The Swordsman's high-tension conflict with the Avengers continues! But even with Iron Man's good word to vouch for him, will the Avengers let him join the team?

84.text: Nothing can stop the Juggernaut, but the X-Men will go down trying! Guest-starring the Human Torch!

88.text: Who is the Swordsman, and what business (or history) does he have with the Avengers? More importantly-is he friend...or foe?

99.text: Which Avenger can best the Commissar, iron-fisted dictator of Sin-Cong, one-on-one? The answer isn't who you'd expect!
